TCR3_ECOLX - Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Resistance to tetracycline by an active tetracycline efflux. This is an energy-dependent process that decreases the accumulation of the antibiotic in whole cells. This protein functions as a metal- tetracycline/H(+) antiporter. From Escherichia coli. This protein is used as a marker in many commonly used cloning vectors, such as pBR322 and pACYC184.

TETR1_ECOLX - Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. TetR is the repressor of the tetracycline resistance element; its N-terminal region forms a helix-turn-helix structure and binds DNA. Binding of tetracycline to TetR reduces the repressor affinity for the tetracycline resistance gene (tetA) promoter operator sites. From Escherichia coli.
